<div><big>about the shea tree</big><div>
<div>The shea tree(vitellaria paradoxa) or karite in french is a<div>
<div>wild fruit found in the savannahs of sub Sahara Africa.<div>
<div>in Nigeria, it is fondly called Okwuma in Igbo,<div>
<div>Okwume in Idoma, Okwomi in Gbagyi, Ori-oyo in Yoruba,<div>
<div>Mankade in Hausa.
<div><div>    
<div><div>
<div><div>
<div>The tree takes about 20-25 years to mature brfore fruiting, it is<div>
<div>not cultivated, it is Gods gift to Africam woman hence called<div>
<div>womens Gold.<div>
<div>The trees are found in 16 countries of Africa namely:Nigeria,<div>
<div>Senegal,Mali,Burkina Faso,Ghana,Sudan,Ethiopia,Uganda and Democratic<div>
<div>Republic of congo.The leaves, bark,fruit and roots are medicinal.<div> 
